Write a program in Spring Boot,
add intergation into sql database then Read the data in the collection and then Flatten to write into mongoDb

steps:
1)Create application manually or through spring initializer

2)Create a package in src\main\java\com.example.Name\ called model, then create Java class

3)In the class declare your variables then set and/or return them
  eg
     @NonNull
     private int ISBN;
     
     public Book(int ISBN){
        super();
        this.ISBN = ISBN;
     }
      
     public int getISBN(){
        return ISBN;
     } 
     
4)Create a repository to access the data. Create package in src\main\java\com.example.Name\ called repository then create Java interface

5)Extend CrudRepositiry in the interface
   eg
       //CrudRepository interface requires the entity class and its ID type
       public interface BookRepository extends CrudRepository<Book, Long>{
       }
 
 6)Create a RestController. Create package in src\main\java\com.example.Name\ called controller then create Java class
 
 7)Add @RequestMapping("className") and @RestController
 
 8)Inject the repository in the Controller Class
   eg
      private final BookRepository repository;

      public BookController(BookRepository repository){
           this.repository = repository;
      }
 
